  "datePublished": "2026-03-29",
  "description": "An extension is a morphism that builds something bigger out of something smaller by adding new structure. It requires objects to extend between, and composition to chain extensions together.\nExtension preserves structure — everything the original had is still there in the extended version. You can always recover the original by forgetting what was added. A forgetful functor does exactly this: it strips the added structure and gives you back what you started with.\n",
